==English==
===Etymology===
Ecclesiastical Latin [[homousianus]], from Greek [[ὁμοουσιος]], from [[ὁμο]] ‘same’ + [[ουσια]] ‘essence’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/hɒməʊ'u:zɪən/}}

===Adjective===
{{en-ad|homoousian}}
# having the same [[essence]] or [[substance]], especially with reference to the first and second persons of the [[Trinity]]

